 ER24 paramedics arrived on the scene and found that a 57-year-old man and 45-year-old woman had taken refuge in the reception area. Paramedics assessed the two patients and found that they had sustained numerous stings said ER24 spokesman Russel Meiring.Both victims were treated for their injuries and then transported to Jabulani Hospital for further treatment he said.It was understood that two other men had also sustained numerous bee stings he added. This occurred while they were cutting the grass nearby and apparently disturbed the bee hive. Both men were transported privately to a nearby hospital Meiring said.